 {"id":"bd-yx9r.11.1","title":"Implement database client-family parity","description":"Port the database clients that upstream exports: sqlite, postgres, mysql, pool, and transaction surfaces. Messaging clients move to a dedicated sibling task so backend-specific lifecycle, retry, and shutdown behavior can be specified cleanly.","design":"Implementation should build on the network/service/transport work with explicit resource, retry, and shutdown behavior. Include fail-closed unsupported-backend behavior where full parity is not immediately achievable.","acceptance_criteria":"A. Public database module families exist or explicitly fail closed with documented limits.\\nB. Tests cover connection lifecycle, pool behavior, transaction/error semantics, and backend-specific shutdown/retry paths.\\nC. Logged integration or e2e flows exercise at least one database backend with artifact-rich diagnostics.","notes":"Keep messaging semantics in a separate bead so queueing, streaming, and broker failures get their own acceptance coverage.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:38:46.645751120Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-19T18:00:20.293364170Z","closed_at":"2026-03-19T18:00:20.292563966Z","close_reason":"Database client-family implemented: db.c/h with connection pool, query execution, transaction lifecycle (begin/commit/rollback), result set with cursor navigation, column indexing, and typed value constructors (null/int/text/float). 9 unit tests.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["crate-parity","database","messaging"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.11.1","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:27:29.106794382Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.11.1","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.11","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:38:46.645751120Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.11.1","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:27:30.170290645Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.11.1","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:27:31.223249840Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.11.1","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.7.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:39:55.865249081Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.11.1","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.8.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:39:57.150247491Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.11.1","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.9.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:39:58.532842309Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
-{"id":"bd-yx9r.11.2","title":"Implement distributed runtime, snapshot, assignment, and recovery parity","description":"Upstream distributed surfaces include snapshots, assignment/distribution, bridge/recovery, encoding, and consistent hashing. ANSI C has no comparable public distributed layer today, but it is part of the exported crate surface.","design":"Port the distributed family in a staged but substantive way, grounded in explicit semantics for remote cancellation, snapshot continuity, assignment, and recovery. The result should be testable in deterministic/lab modes and native integration flows.","acceptance_criteria":"A. Public distributed modules exist with explicit contracts for snapshot/assignment/recovery/bridge behavior.\\nB. Tests cover deterministic distributed scenarios, recovery behavior, and failure artifacts.\\nC. Logged scenario packs show distributed bring-up, reassignment, fault, and recovery flows.","notes":"Depends heavily on D2, D3, E2, F, G1, and H.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:38:48.220720197Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-13T22:29:54.943144644Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["crate-parity","distributed"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.11.2","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:27:32.260095746Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.11.2","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.11","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:38:48.220720197Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.11.2","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.11.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:40:00.098273920Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.11.2","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.11.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:29:54.942200167Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.11.2","depends_