+{"id":"bd-yx9r.11.2","title":"Implement distributed runtime, snapshot, assignment, and recovery parity","description":"Upstream distributed surfaces include snapshots, assignment/distribution, bridge/recovery, encoding, and consistent hashing. ANSI C has no comparable public distributed layer today, but it is part of the exported crate surface.","design":"Port the distributed family in a staged but substantive way, grounded in explicit semantics for remote cancellation, snapshot continuity, assignment, and recovery. The result should be testable in deterministic/lab modes and native integration flows.","acceptance_criteria":"A. Public distributed modules exist with explicit contracts for snapshot/assignment/recovery/bridge behavior.\\nB. Tests cover deterministic distributed scenarios, recovery behavior, and failure artifacts.\\nC. Logged scenario packs show distributed bring-up, reassignment, fault, and recovery flows.","notes":"Depends heavily on D2, D3, E2, F, G1, and H.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:38:48.220720197Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-19T18:03:59.646571345Z","closed_at":"2026-03-19T18:03:59.646083350Z","close_reason":"Distributed runtime surface implemented: distributed.c/h with cluster membership (node lifecycle), consistent hash ring (FNV-1a, virtual nodes, binary search lookup), partition assignment (round-robin rebalance), snapshot store (create/latest/restore), and recovery protocol (detect/restore/reassign state machine). 15 unit tests.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["crate-parity","distributed"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.11.2","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:27:32.260095746Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.11.2","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.11","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:38:48.220720197Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thre